The problem is in the details, he added.
Goldman Sachs bank faced criticism after setting aside almost $17 billion (nearly CZK 300 billion) for bonuses in the first three quarters of this year.
The total sum of bonuses in the entity for this year, according to the Reuters agency, probably exceeds, despite the measure announced today, 20 billion dollars.
High bonuses in the banking sector became, with the advent of the financial crisis, a sensitive issue in politics.
Britain announced on Wednesday that it plans to tax bankers bonuses over £25,000 (about CZK 712,000) at a flat rate of 50 percent.
France is also preparing similar measures.
This year, women received the Nobel Prizes in all categories except physics.
Five women, a record number, were awarded this year's Nobel Prizes in Stockholm by King Carl XVI Gustaf of Sweden, in specialised categories and in literature.
In addition to the four women scientists, the winners included a German writer of Romanian origin, Herta Müller.
The Nobel Prize in medicine was awarded to two American biologists, Elizabeth Blackburn and Carol Greider, and to their compatriot Jack Szostak for their work on chromosomes.
The Nobel Prize in chemistry was awarded to Israeli Ada Jonath and Americans Venkatraman Ramakrishna and Thomas Steitz for their explanation of the structure and function of ribosomes.
The last award, the Nobel Prize in Economics, was given to American economist Elinor Ostrom and her compatriot Oliver Williamson for their analysis of an economic report.
The only specialized category without a female winner was Physics.
The prize was awarded to Charles Kao for his research into optical cables, and to George Smith and Willard Boyle for their invention of the CCD chip, which is the basis of all digital cameras, fax machines and telescopes.
Each laureate received the diploma, the Nobel medal and the certificate of the money received.
This sum in each category is up to SEK 10 million (approximately SEK 25 million).
In the event of several winners in each category, the prize shall be shared among them.
