Employees can claim the bonus for overtime or they can take a day off on December 28, i.e. extend the Christmas holidays by one day, Vaněk said.
In addition, all employees on Saturday shifts will receive travel and food money.
Because the overtime was the most urgent and problematic point of the comments and complaints of the trade unionists and strikers, who stopped the manufacturing last week, the management yesterday afternoon decided to immediately cancel all overtime for the month of December, Vaněk mentioned.
Employees at the car factory were forced to work two hours more in addition to eight-hour shifts and this situation persisted almost every day until last week.
After the agreement is signed the unions will cancel the emergency strike.
