The UN-sponsored climate conference, which has been characterized so far by defiant posturing and mutual recriminations, has captured renewed attention on Friday with the release of a document that envisions ambitious greenhouse gas reductions over the next 40 years, with industrialized nations bearing most of the burden in the short term.
