Some of the countries most vulnerable to the impact of climate change indicated they would continue to push for a legally binding treaty in Copenhagen, although most of the main participants say the talks will produce at most a political agreement.
The Alliance of Small Island States, which has 43 members, drew up a preliminary 24-page treaty proposal early Friday morning.
